    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given that ASTM F1717 is the applicable regulatory standard and defines a single standardized test condition; no alternative condition is clinically or regulatorily mandated. All three QoIs pass quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96; percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is judged sufficiently credible for its intended use in supporting the 510(k) submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
